    <note>Chen(1) Bing [14292] Ye Shi quotes Bing's son, Qiqing [10881], who traces ancestry back to Shi(2) [12823], an early Yingchuan Chen(1). Qiqing claims kin with the northern Song Linhai jinshi, Chen(1) Yifan [10547] and Yixu [10548]. No describes his grandfathers (ie. grandfather and granduncle), Bin(3) [24360] and Bing(6) [24361] as classicist teachers (ru xiansheng). Qiqing also stated that the lineage moved from Wuzhou to Taizhou, Yifan and Yixu being the first distinguished names (zhuming) of the lineage. I reconstruct the lineage as follows: Chen(1) L [24358] was a lineal descendant of Shi(2) [12823], and moved from Wuzhou to Taizhou, Linhai county, Chen(1) M [24359] as the father of Yifan and Yixu and as the the great grandfather of Bin(3), Bing(6), and Zhu(3) [14406] (designated in Chicheng zhi, 34.3b as the younger brother of Qiqing's grandfather), and these three as all uncles of Bing, although Bin(3) or Bing(6) must have been his father. Ye Shi, WJ, 25.493-4. CBD, 3, 2458.</note>
